    },
    {
      "paragraph_name": "COPAU1A",
      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "This DFHMDI macro defines the map COPAU1A, which represents a single screen layout within the COPAU01 mapset. It specifies the screen's column and line position (COLUMN=1, LINE=1) and its size (SIZE=(24,80)), defining a standard 24x80 screen. The map contains various DFHMDF macros that define the individual fields on the screen, including labels, input fields, and output fields. These fields are positioned using the POS parameter, and their lengths are defined using the LENGTH parameter. Attributes such as color (COLOR), intensity (ATTRB), and initial values (INITIAL) are also specified for each field. The map includes fields for displaying transaction details (TRNNAME), current date (CURDATE), program name (PGMNAME), current time (CURTIME), card number (CARDNUM), authorization date (AUTHDT), authorization time (AUTHTM), authorization response (AUTHRSP), response reason (AUTHRSN), authorization code (AUTHCD), amount (AUTHAMT), POS entry mode (POSEMD), authorization source (AUTHSRC), MCC code (MCCCD), card expiration date (CRDEXP), authorization type (AUTHTYP), transaction ID (TRNID), match status (AUTHMTC), fraud status (AUTHFRD), merchant details (MERNAME, MERID, MERCITY, MERST, MERZIP), and an error message area (ERRMSG).",
